    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a clear emphasis on high-upside speed and favorable sequencing. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.13) and **James Wood** (75.23) headline our production, capitalizing on the generous 5.10 xERA of the opposing starter facing **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and the high-leverage order position of **James Wood**. **Corbin Carroll** (72.54) remains a primary focal point despite a moderate matchup, as his elite profile against Michael King keeps him in the upper echelon of our daily projections. These three are our engines for the day, particularly given our strategic weighting of stolen base potential against pitchers with slower deliveries or favorable conditions. **Tyler Soderstrom** (69.65) also earns a strong recommendation, benefiting from a balanced profile and an optimal #3 spot in the order.\n\nTactical edge-seeking is evident in how we\u2019ve navigated the fringes of the roster. **Brice Turang** (57.33) and **Austin Riley** (56.86) provide stable, strong-side contributions. **Austin Riley** specifically stands out as an interesting case where BvP historical data (60 PA) successfully offset the negative impact of an elite opposing catcher's pop time. Conversely, the decision to bench **Kyle Karros** (33.84) was the most difficult; despite a decent base projection, the combination of a tough 3.04 xERA opponent, a park-factor penalty, and incoming wind rendered his efficiency score too low to justify breaking the 40.0 \"Zebras\" floor. \n\nWe are monitoring a few specific risks heading into first pitch. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (41.10) is currently our most precarious start due to a 45% rain risk in his contest and a difficult matchup against Reid Detmers; while he sits above our floor, his output is highly volatile. Additionally, we are tracking \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Dalton Rushing**, **Luis Campusano**, **Alex Freeland**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Corbin Carroll**. Should these players fall out of their anticipated slots or drop in the batting order, their scores will be re-evaluated against the bench depth of **Trevor Story**, **Max Muncy**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana** to ensure we maintain our daily efficiency targets.",
